                    <ab>[In nomine domini nostri Iesu Christi Dei eterni. <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/21">Berengarius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>. Decentissimum atque sacratissimum fore
                        arbitramur venerabilium <rs key="#Monks">monachis</rs> locorum augustalis
                        opem tribuere dignitatis et subsidium attribuere quietis, quatenus
                        incursionum remotis illecebris pio Domino regulari dediti disciplinae
                        famulari iugiter delectet, et pro nobis atque statu regni nostri
                        fidissimisque optimatibus nostris ipsius clementiam exorare ne pigeat.
                        Itaque omnium fidelium sancte Dei Ecclesie nostrorum scilicet ac futurorum
                        noverit universitas, quia......<rs key="#Intercessory">adiit clementiam
                            nostram</rs>, quatenus venerabili <rs key="#Abbots">abbati</rs>
                        <persName key="#Abbots"><name ref="Aginulfus">Aginulfo</name></persName>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/151"><placeName
                                ref="#places/458">Ebobiensis</placeName>
                            <rs key="#Monasteries">coenobii</rs></orgName> eiusque congregationi
                        ibidem degentibus preceptum iuxta felicium decessorum nostrorum augustorum
                        innovare sanciremus. Nos itaque considerantes aeterne retributionis
                        emolumentum, ob reverentiam beatissimorum apostolorum Petri et Pauli, in
                        quorum honore ipsum monasterium cognoscitur esse fundatum, sanctique
                        Columbani qui ibidem humatus quiescit, libenter adsensum praebuimus, et hanc
                        nostre auctoritatis constitutionem] perenniter et in[mutabiliter]
                        conservandam fieri [iussimus. Per quam concedimus] et secundum augmentum
                        dignissime recordationis domni <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/14">Karoli</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperatoris</rs> senioris et consobrini nostra
                        regali auctoritate sancimus, ut in q[ui]buslibet <rs key="#Pagus">pagis</rs>
                        vel <rs key="#Administrative_units">territoriis</rs> de rebus supradicti
                        cenobii aliqua orta fuerit contentio, cui vera sit <rs key="#Inquisitio"
                            >inquisitio</rs> necessaria, ex nostra fiat auctoritate per [i]don[e]os
                        homines quorum testimonium probabile sit, ne aliqua interveniente incuria
                        vel occasione eadem <rs key="#Churches">ecclesia</rs> de facultatibus suis
                        aliquid cogatur amittere quod ei iuste competit habere. Omnia quoque que
                        inferius notantur inrefragabiliter absque cuiusquam inquietudine seu
                        immutatione concedimus habenda et ordinanda per abbatem qui pro tempore
                        fuerit nostra largitione et eorum electione ipsi sancto loco substitutus
                        secundum Dei voluntatem eorumque in omnibus competentem utilitatem. Id est,
                            <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs> cum <rs key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            >cellulis</rs> infra <rs key="#Natural_landscape">vallem</rs> in qua
                        situm est consistentibus <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#places/492"><orgName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                >Turrem</orgName></placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/491"
                            key="#Cells/hermitages"><orgName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                >Boco</orgName></placeName>, <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#places/493"><orgName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                >Salonianum montana et maritima</orgName></placeName> cum cellulis
                            <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                            >Carice</orgName> et <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                            >Turio</orgName>, <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                            >Carelio</orgName>, <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#places/494"
                                ><orgName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                >Comorga</orgName></placeName> et <rs key="#Cells/hermitages"
                                ><orgName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                >Castellione</orgName></rs>, <rs key="#Cells/hermitages"><orgName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                >Ranci</orgName></rs> cum <rs key="#Cells/hermitages"><orgName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                >Casasco</orgName></rs> et <rs key="#Cells/hermitages"><orgName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                >Caniano</orgName></rs> atque <rs key="#Cells/hermitages"><orgName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                >Brioni</orgName></rs> ac <rs key="#Cells/hermitages"><orgName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                >Vicopontio</orgName></rs>, <rs key="#Cells/hermitages"><orgName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Cells/hermitages"
                                >Virdim</orgName></rs> cum <rs key="#Churches">ecclesia</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/179">Sancti Pauli</orgName> in <placeName
                            ref="#places/466">Niza</placeName> et <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/180">Sancti Albani in Candubri[o]</orgName>,
                            <placeName ref="#places/467"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Montem Longum cum Memoriola</placeName> et omnibus appenditiis suis,
                            <placeName ref="#places/468"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Tovatiam</placeName> cum ecclesia <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/185"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Sancti Pauli in Sartoriano</orgName>, <rs key="#Hay/fodder">Prato
                            Silvano</rs> cum ecclesia <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/184">Sancti Antonini</orgName> et <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/186">Sancti Severi</orgName>, <placeName
                            ref="#places/474"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Pecorari</placeName> cum <placeName ref="#places/475"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Palantas</placeName> et proprio <persName><name ref="Guntelmus"
                                >Guntelmi</name></persName> et <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Paderno</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/476"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Travano</placeName> cum <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Alfiano</placeName> et <placeName ref="#places/477"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Ancariano</placeName> et ecclesia <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Sancti Salvatoris</orgName> in <placeName ref="#places/481"
                            >Clauzano</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/480"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Rovaclas</placeName> et <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >ecclesia in honore sancte Resurrectionis</orgName> cum his que ad eam
                        pertinent, <placeName ref="#places/478"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Aulianum</placeName> cum proprio de <persName><name ref="Fulcherius"
                                >Fulcario</name></persName> et <persName><name ref="Teutrudis"
                                >Teutrude</name></persName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Cassianum</placeName> et <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Casellas</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/479"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Sorlascum</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Luliatica</placeName>, <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Garda</placeName> cum <placeName ref="#places/482"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Aderbassio</placeName>, <placeName ref="#places/483"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Fraxinetum</placeName> et <placeName ref="#places/484"
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >portum Mantuanum</placeName>, propriumque quod <persName><name
                                ref="Sabbatinus Veneticus">Sabatinus Veneticus</name></persName> in
                            <placeName ref="#places/485">Quomaclo</placeName> sancto Columbano
                        tradidit, proprium quoque quod <persName key="#Bishops"><name
                                ref="Teudaldus">Teudaldus</name></persName> et <persName
                            key="#Bishops"><name ref="Theobaldus">Teopaldus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs> ipsi monasterio tradiderunt, <rs
                            key="#Hospitals">scenodochium</rs> aetiam in Papia cum [omnibus] ad eum
                        pertinentibus <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >Perledum</placeName>, <placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                >Medei</placeName>, <placeName
                                    key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                    >Farinariam</placeName>, <placeName
                                        key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                        >Crucem</placeName> atque <placeName
                                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                                            >Genuam</placeName>. Omnia
                        igitur hec superius que inserta sunt, sicut ad eundem sanctum et venerabilem
                        locum delegata et tradita noscuntur, ita cum omni integritate, cum omnibus
                        ad eum pertinentibus, cum mass[a]riciis vel famil[i]is, seu cunctis
                        adiacentiis sub omni integritate absque ulla diminutione [seu] subtractione,
                        et queque deinceps ipsi sana industria vel quorumlibet Chr[istian]orum
                        legitima collatione acquirere potuerint inconvulsa et perpetua stabilitate
                        coneedimus haberi, possideri, et ad votum ipsorum religiose rati[o]nabiliter
                        et Deo placite ordinari. Sed et privilegia apostolica auctoritate eidem
                        sancto loco largita per hoc pragmaticum confirmamus, et ut nullus
                        episcoporum vel ex quolibet ecclesiastico ordine violare vel irrumpere
                        attentet omnino interdicimus. Igitur quia pro summa rei publice necessitate
                        pacisque tranquillitate quandam divisionem de rebus iam fati cenobii ad oram
                        fieri permisimus, iubemus atque omnimodis statuimus, ut de illa parte quam
                        in usus monachorum delegavimus interim, dum Domino auxiliante ad pristinum
                        revocetur statum, nullus iudex publicus nullus missus discurrens aliquam
                        sepe fatis monachis eorumque familiis violentiam vel inquietudine inferre
                        presumat, quos cum omnibus rebus et familiis sub nostra nos constat
                        recepisse emun[i]tate et mundeburdo. Si quis vero hominum ipsius monasterii
                        utilitatibus famulantium ingenuus commendatus sive servus aliquid
                        commiserit, unde fiscus noster quippiam sperare possit, totum hoc parti
                        ipsius loci sancti concedimus et ne a quoquam exigatur penitus abnegamus.
                        Quicumque vero aliquid horum violare presumpserit, sciat se pene
                        persolvendarum LX libras auri optimi eidem loco esse multandum et insuper
                        nostra offensione plectendum. Nullas quoque redibitiones aut publicas
                        excubias, nullas paradas vel angarias facere sive persolvere cogantur,
                        nullas pontium novas vel veteres structiones seu restructiones agere vel
                        revovare conpellantur. Que nos universa idcirco concessimus et perdonavimus,
                        ut omnipotenti Domino pro nostra totiusque regno nostri augmento et
                        stabilimento devotius, placidius ac delectabilius omni exclusa necessitatis
                        occasione valeant supplicare. Ut autem hec nostre cessionis preceptio rata
                        ac stabilis per futura tempora maneat, manu nostra subter firmavimus et
                        anulo nostro iussimus [s]igillari. Signum (M) domni Berengarii
                        [g]loriosissimi regis. Petrus notarius iussione regia recognovi [et
                        subscripsi.] Data [….....] a[nno] i[incarnationis] D[omini DCCC]LXXXVIII,
                        anno ver[o regni] domni Berengarii gloriosissimi regis I, indictione VI.
                        Actum C[urt]e Alta curte regia. [In Dei nomine feliciter, amen.]</ab>
